भारत सरकार, भारत तथा उसके हर भाग की सुरक्षा सुनिश्चित करने के लिए जिम्मेवार है । सशस्त्र सेनाओं की सर्वोच्च कमान राष्ट्रपति के पास निहित होती है । राष्ट्रीय सुरक्षा की जिम्मेवारी मंत्रिमंडल के पास निहित होती है । यह जिम्मेवारी रक्षा मंत्रालय के जरिए निभाई जाती है जो सशस्त्र सेनाओं को देश की सुरक्षा के संबंध में उनकी जिम्मेवारी निभाने के लिए नीति संबंधी ढांचा तथा साधन उपलब्ध कराता है। रक्षा मंत्री रक्षा मंत्रालय के प्रमुख होते हैं। रक्षा मंत्रालय का मुख्य कार्य रक्षा और सुरक्षा संबंधी सभी मामलों पर सरकार के नीति-निर्देश प्राप्त करना तथा उन्हें लागू करने के लिए सेना मुख्यालयों, अंतर-सेवा संगठ

A Story in Every
Walk of Life
Read the extraordinary stories of Naval community members who have re-defined what it means to inspire.
Dr. Avantika Kekan
Dr. Avantika Kekan is an anaesthetist who seamlessly blends her medical career with a passion for adventure. A trained mountaineer, she has conquered peaks like Mt. Kang Yatse I (6,400m) and Mt. Stok Kangri (6,153m). Her latest feat was summiting an unnamed 6,063m peak near Shinkun La via a new route, now named Nirjala. She has also completed numerous high-altitude treks in the Himalayas.
Read Full Story
Gursharan Kaur
Gursharan Kaur is an accomplished 10m Air Pistol shooter. She began her journey at the Air Rifle and Pistol Shooting Club at the Indian Naval Academy in 2020 and has pursued the sport with dedication. She has earned several accolades:
Read Full Story
Priyanka Jagtap
Priyanka Jagtap, a proud Naval officer’s wife and mother of two, is passionate about horse riding. Despite the challenges and risks, she embraces the sport with determination, drawing inspiration from the saying, “Every fall is a lesson, and every ride is a journey of resilience”.
Her fascination with horse riding began in Wellington, but she truly pursued it in Visakhapatnam, where she trained rigorously. Inspired by Monica Saxena, Captain of the women’s Polo team, Priyanka believes leadership earns respect — even from horses. Her goal is to master Polo, despite its exclusivity.
An engineer by qualification, Priyanka adapts her career to opportunities. She currently works as a resume writer assisting veterans while also exploring art, swimming, golf and guitar. For her, riding a horse is like flying without wings — a pursuit of confidence, strength and endless possibilities.
Read Full Story
Laxmipriya Mahapatra
Laxmipriya Mahapatra is a baking instructor at the NWWA center in Rameshwaram. A Zoology graduate with Montessori training, she balanced family responsibilities as a Naval wife while nurturing her passion for teaching and cooking. Encouraged by friends and family, she explored hobby classes at NWWA, eventually discovering her love for baking.
